4.title: Of Corsets Fashion
4.plot: Celebrate a woman's figure by incorporating a corset into a high-fashion look.

5.title: On The Prowl
5.plot: The all-winners season continues with high fashion inspired by zoo animals for a wild night out.

1.title: Return to the Runway
1.plot: 13 of Project Runway's most talented and controversial designers return for a second chance at victory. New host supermodel Angela Lindvall reveals an All Stars twist to what all designers love to hate--the unconventional challenge! The All Stars are greeted by new mentor, Marie Claire's Joanna Coles before facing new judges Georgina Chapman and Isaac Mizrahi.

2.title: A Night at the Opera
2.plot: The All Stars have just 24 hours to create glamorous ball gowns for a night at the Opera. Guest judges are kings of the red carpet, fashion duo Mark Badgley and James Mischka.

3.title: Patterning for Piggy
3.plot: Miss Piggy takes charge as client and guest judge when the All Stars create a cocktail dress for the Muppets' most demanding diva. Will the designers live up to the high standards of this international fashion icon?

4.title: Good Taste Tastes Good
4.plot: Fashion icon Diane Von Furstenberg joins Angela on the Runway to reveal the fastest challenge in Runway history. It's a race against time as the top ten All Stars have only six hours to create a colorful look for supermodel Miranda Kerr.

5.title: Clothes Off Your Back
5.plot: The All Stars take to the streets of New York to convince total strangers to part with their clothes in the name of fashion. Their muse's outfits are ripped apart and reborn in the hands of an All Star.

6.title: Fashion Face Off
6.plot: The eight remaining All Stars compete head to head in a sportswear challenge for one of the four seasons. Guest judge Cynthia Rowley.

7.title: Puttin' on the Glitz
7.plot: It's all about Broadway baby, when the designers compete for their Broadway debut. The award winning composer of "Wicked" Stephen Schwartz, challenges the All Stars to design an outfit for the Broadway musical "Godspell.

8.title: O! Say, Can You Sew?
8.plot: While at the United Nations headquarters, the designers must choose flags as inspiration for creating dresses.

9.title: When I Have My Dress in Lights
9.plot: The remaining All Stars are confronted with their toughest challenge yet; use lighting technology to create an avant garde design to be judged by music legend Pharrell Williams. The lights are dimmed for a Runway show unlike ever seen before!

10.title: Let's Get Down to Business
10.plot: To determine which three All Stars make it to the finale, the designers get a lesson in the business of fashion. The winning outfit is produced by designer Nanette Lepore and sold nationwide for charity.

11.title: Finale Part 1
11.plot: The final three All Stars have just four days to create a signature collection for a VIP red carpet Runway show. After a visit to Joanna Coles at Marie Claire headquarters plus some surprise visitors to the workroom, Angela reveals the final All Stars twist.

12.title: Finale Part 2
12.plot: The moment of truth arrives for three final All Stars as they present their signature collections to a VIP Runway show crowd. Guest judges include fashion icon Tommy Hilfiger. Who will claim the biggest prize in Runway history and be crowned the first `Project Runway All Stars' winner?

1.title: Redemption on the Runway
1.plot: 13 of Project Runway s most creative and contentious designers return for a second chance at the biggest prize ever. In the season's first team challenge, the designers flaunt their fashion attitudes in more ways than one.

2.title: Put on Your Dancing Shoes
2.plot: The All Stars are tasked with recreating and updating a 70's disco style using Nine West shoes of their choosing as inspiration! Designer Rafe Totengco guest judges.

3.title: Up Your Aerosol
3.plot: Graffiti artists help the designers tag their fabric with spray paint from which they must create wearable art. Designers Robert Tagliapietra and Jeffrey Costello serve as guest judges.

4.title: Made in the USA Today
4.plot: Social media and fashion collide when the All Stars must draw inspiration for their runway designs from images sent to them by readers of USA Today. Guest judges are designer Charlotte Ronson and fashion blogging sensation Tavi Gevinson.

5.title: You've Got Male
5.plot: Nine designers struggle with creating an avant garde, androgynous look when a twist has them working double-time for guest judges Jason Wu and Robert Rodriguez.

6.title: Green Dress for Red Carpet
6.plot: The All Stars gather at NYC's Highline and are challenged to create a red carpet gown using only green, eco-friendly fabrics and materials. The legendary Diane Von Furstenberg guest judges.

7.title: An Unconventional Nightmare Before Christmas
7.plot: The seven remaining designers play naughty or nice in the fan-favorite unconventional challenge that brings them to a Christmas decor emporium. The designers will have to impress guest judges singer Kylie Minogue and television personality LaLa Anthony.

8.title: Flapper Fashion Face-Off
8.plot: The final six All Stars are tasked with designing a look for one of three vintage 1920's events. To make matters worse, they must face off against each other in pairs of two in this season's Fashion Face Off!

9.title: There's No Business Like Sew Business
9.plot: High Fashion meets a Retail Budget! The five remaining All Stars must create a ready to wear look with a "wow factor," while also meeting a retail budget.

10.title: All Stars and Stripes
10.plot: The Project Runway designers pay their tribute the armed forces! The four remaining designers are paired with four female veterans from an array of different military branches.

11.title: Couture De France
11.plot: The designers go international! For the first time ever in Project Runway history, the designers retire sketching at 1407 for a day of sketching in Paris at the Eiffel tower!

12.title: Go Big or Go Home
12.plot: The three remaining designers compete in the finale for a chance to win a life-altering grand prize! However, because this is All Stars, the final three designers only get four days and an hour and a half at Mood, to complete a full mini collection.

1.title: You Got Punked!
1.plot: The competition is tougher than ever as three winners of Project Runway return to defend their titles. The task at hand--to create a fashion-forward punk look inspired and judged by punk rock icon Debbie Harry of Blondie.

2.title: Bitten by the Fashion Bug
2.plot: At the American Museum of Natural History, creepy crawly arachnids and insects serve as inspiration for the designers to create an avant-garde look. Guest judges are Project Runway season 9 winner, Anya Ayoung Chee, and jewelry designer Jennifer Meyer.

3.title: Slip Into Something Sexier
3.plot: Signature cocktails at Jay Z's legendary 40/40 Club stir up ideas for runway worthy cocktail dresses. Guest judges are interior designer Nate Berkus and designer Rebecca Minkoff.

4.title: Keepin' It Classy
4.plot: It's back to school for the remaining eight designers in this fan-favorite unconventional challenge to create high impact fashion from materials found in an elementary school classroom. Guest judges are actors Michael Urie and Gabourey Sidibe.

5.title: Partners in Crime
5.plot: The designers pair up to create young modern looks inspired by the 1930s and Lifetime's new mini-series "Bonnie & Clyde." Guest judges are Austin Scarlett, designer Elie Tahari, and supermodel Bar Refaeli.

6.title: Marge Madness
6.plot: America's favorite housewife, Marge Simpson, turns to the All Stars to design a date night dress for an exciting evening out on the town with Homer. Guest judges Anthony Ryan Auld, designer Stacey Bendet and actress Abigail Breslin help to determine whose dress Marge will wear on a future episode of "The Simpsons.

7.title: As Sewn on TV
7.plot: Six remaining designers are whisked away by helicopter to QVC's headquarters in Pennsylvania where they're challenged to design a stunning red carpet gown. Mondo Guerra, QVC's Lisa Robertson, and actress Elisabeth Moss are guest judges.

8.title: #Nina's Trending
8.plot: Project Runway goes global as the designers team up with some of the most influential fashion bloggers in the world to identify a new trend for 2014. Guest judges are Nina Garcia, Christian Siriano and Calvin Klein's Francisco Costa.

9.title: Fashion Cents
9.plot: Fashion and commerce collide as the All Stars work with design house Milly to create ready-to-wear looks to be sold for charity and the designers face a shocking twist on the runway. Guest judges are Kristin Chenoweth, Nick Cannon and Milly Designer Michelle Smith.

10.title: Are U.N. Or Are You Out?
10.plot: In the Season Finale, designers present collections inspired by their own heritage at a VIP runway show at the world headquarters of the United Nations. Project Runway's Zac Posen and guest judge Gayle King help to crown the winner.

11.title: Reunion Special: Season 3
11.plot: Alyssa Milano reunites the 11 All Star designers to reflect upon the season and goes behind the scenes with exclusives, surprises and some unfinished business! The special will also include a surprise appearance by Debbie Harry, unseen footage and a Simpsons exclusive.

1.title: Made in Manhattan
1.plot: Project Runway All Stars designers return for the biggest season yet. For their first challenge, designers must create collections inspired by New York's uptown or downtown scene.

2.title: The Art of Construction
2.plot: A construction site forces designers to create feminine fashion from masculine materials for the notorious unconventional challenge.

3.title: Something Wicked This Way Comes
3.plot: With exclusive access to the Broadway musical "Wicked", the All Stars face off to design couture inspired fashion. Betsey Johnson and Modern Family's Ariel Winter guest judge.

4.title: Wear Your Heart on Your Sleeve
4.plot: Emotions run high as Nina Garcia returns to judge colorful party dresses inspired by the designers' personal relationships.

5.title: Designing for the Duchess
5.plot: The designers meet British royalty in London, England as inspiration for winter wear. Debra Messing guest judges.

6.title: Luck Be a Lady
6.plot: The stakes are high as the All Stars designers roll dice on the runway for a fashion gamble.

7.title: Mix and Match.com
7.plot: Love is in the air as the All Stars design looks for Match.com singles on first dates. Orange Is The New Black's Laverne Cox guest judges.

8.title: Making a Splash
8.plot: Elegant resort wear with attention grabbing swimsuits. But first the designers must collect their fabric from under the water! Nigel Barker guest judges.

9.title: Sketching with Sharks
9.plot: Underwater marine life provides inspiration for avant-garde fashion. But which designer doubles the budget by swimming with the sharks?

10.title: Versatile Tops and Bottoms
10.plot: Alyssa and the judges take over Times Square to school the designers in the business of fashion for a QVC separates challenge.

11.title: Always the Bridesmaid
11.plot: Marchesa's showroom inspires bridesmaid dresses for a real wedding ceremony officiated by Alyssa on the runway. Cat Deeley guests.

12.title: Some Like It Hot Dog
12.plot: Marilyn Monroe's timeless beauty inspires dazzling red carpet gowns. And a Hollywood legend pays a special visit to the workroom.

13.title: 4 Seasons in One Finale
13.plot: The All Stars finalists design collections representing all 4 seasons of the year. Zac Posen and Mira Sorvino join the judges and a VIP audience to crown the winner. Season finale.

1.title: What Makes an All Star
1.plot: 13 All Stars return for the toughest season yet. Designers tap into their past to create a look inspired by a life moment that kick started their fashion career.

2.title: Let It Flow
2.plot: The contestants must great an outfit that has movement. The models will walk down the runway with a wind machine.

3.title: A Little Bit Country, a Little Bit Rock n Roll
3.plot: Country music super group "Little Big Town" team up the designers to create "opposites attract" red carpet gowns for the Academy of Country Music Awards.

4.title: Fashion 911
4.plot: The Unconventional Challenge finds the designers turning New York City emergency services materials into runway-worthy looks.

5.title: Birthday Suits
5.plot: The designers must create winter wear to keep uninhibited naturists toasty warm on the naked runaway.

6.title: Going for Baroque
6.plot: Designers create couture-inspired gowns that celebrate Baroque fashion. Marchesa's Keren Craig and Supermodel Coco Rocha guest judge.

7.title: Bait and Stitch
7.plot: The All Stars must use another designer's chosen fabric to create evening resort wear. Megan Hilty guests.

8.title: Once Upon a Runway
8.plot: Broadway's `Finding Neverland' star tasks the designers to reimagine modern looks for classic fairytale characters. Kesha and Brad Goreski guest judge.

9.title: A Touch of Style
9.plot: Sports and fashion combine as designers create high-end leisure wear inspired by the "Touch by Alyssa Milano" line. Kristin Cavallari guests.

10.title: Rebel with a Cause
10.plot: Zac Posen and Debi Mazar join the judges to critique sophisticated summer-chic looks with a badass edge.

11.title: State of the Art
11.plot: Tensions run high as designers are pushed to the limit to create avant-garde fashion inspired by contemporary art. Style icon Boy George guests.

12.title: Prince of Prints
12.plot: Four surprise guests return to advise the All Stars as they create print-on-print looks for Nina Garcia. A shock challenge on the runway has two designers battling to make the finale.

13.title: New York State of Mind
13.plot: Atop the new World Trade Center, the All Stars are challenged to create collections inspired by New York City. Debra Messing joins the judges to crown the winner. Season finale.

1.title: Rookies vs. Vets
1.plot: 8 All Star Rookies and 8 returning All Star Veterans battle to create cohesive collections in the biggest season in All Stars' history.

2.title: Damsels in Distress
2.plot: Designers tear, dye and burn to create distressed fashion for a post-apocalyptic runway. Danielle Brooks guests.

3.title: Perfect Pairings
3.plot: Designers pair up to create fashion inspired by food and wine pairings. Whoopi Goldberg joins the judges for All Stars' first ever double elimination.

4.title: Balls Out!
4.plot: In the notorious unconventional challenge, designers use all types of balls to create modern day "ball gowns." Kacey Musgraves guests.

5.title: Fashion's New Superheroes
5.plot: Designers create looks to celebrate a woman's inner superhero. Supermodel Karolina Kurkova guests.

6.title: Thrown for a Loop by Betty
6.plot: Betty Boop joins Alyssa on the runway to challenge the designers to create young, chic Hollywood looks. Rebecca Minkoff guests.

7.title: A Kick in the Astro
7.plot: RuPaul and Jesse Tyler Ferguson join the judging panel for a spectacular avant-garde runway.

8.title: Mizrahi Madness
8.plot: Isaac Mizrahi's exhibit serves as inspiration for colorful party looks. Legendary supermodel Carmen Dell'Orefice is a guest judge.

9.title: Posen on the Red Carpet
9.plot: Zac Posen invites the designers into his personal studio to gather material for red carpet looks that showcase a signature technique. Zac Posen and Rosie Perez guest judge.

10.title: Rock Your Face Off
10.plot: Designers face off against one another to create performance wear for a music superstar. Olivia Culpo guests.

11.title: Nina's Crushing It
11.plot: Nina Garcia challenges the designers to create resort wear inspired by different Candy Crush lands. Nina Garcia and Kelly Osborne guest judge.

12.title: History in the Making
12.plot: At the Smithsonian in Washington, DC, designers are challenged to create six-piece collections. A surprise runway sends one designer home early. Dita Von Teese and Zanna Roberts Rassi guests.

13.title: Making Fashion History
13.plot: The final three designers race to create seven-piece collections that make their mark in fashion history. Catherine Zeta-Jones and Zac Posen guest judge. Season finale.

locations: New York City, New York, USA
imdb.title: Project Runway All Stars
plot: Past designers come back to compete for another chance to be the winner of Project Runway.
